# Fitness Tracker App - Development Rules

## Platform & Technology
- **Primary Platform**: iOS (iPhone)
- **Future Support**: Android (build with cross-platform compatibility in mind)
- **Framework**: React Native or similar cross-platform framework
- **Testing**: High-quality test coverage required to prevent regressions

## Core Features
1. **Workout Import**: Text/Markdown-based format that LLMs can easily generate
2. **In-Workout Tracking**:
   - Mark off sets as completed
   - Built-in timers (rest periods, workout duration)
3. **Workout History**: Track past workouts
4. **Exercise History**: Track progress per exercise over time

## Design Requirements
- **All screens**: Support both light and dark mode
- **Mobile-first**: Optimized for mobile experience
- **No web support**: Focus on native mobile experience initially

## Development Standards
- Write comprehensive tests for all features
- Follow mobile UI/UX best practices
- Keep code modular for future Android support
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow accessibility guidelines

## Code Quality
- Clean, maintainable code
- Proper error handling
- Consistent code style
- Document complex logic

## Deployment & CI/CD
- **GitHub Actions**: Automated testing and builds
- **EAS Build**: Expo Application Services for iOS builds
- **TestFlight**: Alpha/beta distribution via App Store Connect
- **Release Process**: Use GitHub releases (not direct tags) to trigger deployments
